brzlfqYRBCCTqKBZ2xoA.jpeg","originalWidth":1200,"originalHeight":675}},{"name":"09ea","type":1,"text":"Scholastic publishes these concise, child-friendly guides to the game. Two of them are among the best-selling books of 2014 so far, on a short list with titles like The Fault in Our Stars and The Goldfinch. To me, they are the most salient symbol of the game’s success.","markups":[{"type":3,"start":87,"end":130,"href":"http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/bookselling/article/63195-ya-tops-nielsen-and-kindle-lists-for-2014-so-far.html","title":"","rel":""},{"type":2,"start":165,"end":187},{"type":2,"start":192,"end":207}]},{"name":"018a","type":1,"text":"Imagine yourself a child. Imagine yourself given one of these books: not merely a story of exploration and adventure, but a manual to such.","markups":[{"type":2,"start":82,"end":87},{"type":2,"start":124,"end":130}]},{"name":"2ed5","type":4,"text":"","markups":[],"layout":1,"metadata":{"id":"1*FkJK1Xumbwf1o5ys3vbBbw.jpeg","originalWidth":1200,"originalHeight":675}},{"name":"7405","type":1,"text":"Imagine yourself acquiring the keys to a mutable world in which you can explore caves, fight spiders, build castles, ride pigs, blow up mountains, construct aqueducts to carry water to your summer palace… anything.","markups":[]},{"name":"4cf1","type":1,"text":"Imagine yourself a child, in possession of the secret knowledge.","markups":[]},{"name":"d312","type":1,"text":"This wouldn’t be enough on its own. Obscure techniques have been a part of video games from the beginning; Nintendo Power surely had a dusting of secret knowledge. What’s different here is that Minecraft connects this lure to the objective not of beating the game, but making more of the game.","markups":[{"type":2,"start":107,"end":121},{"type":2,"start":194,"end":203},{"type":2,"start":276,"end":280}]},{"name":"9efe","type":1,"text":"“Game” doesn’t even do it justice. What we’re really talking about here is a generative, networked sys